---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Distributed Lock SDK"
  description="A best-effort distributed lock and debounce SDK built on Upstash Redis."
>
  <article class="p-6 lg:p-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <a href="/shipped" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-charcoal-muted dark:text-sand-muted hover:text-accent dark:hover:text-accent-light transition-colors mb-8">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M7 16l-4-4m0 0l4-4m-4 4h18" />
      </svg>
      Back to shipped work
    </a>

    <header class="mb-10">
      <div class="case-cover mb-8"><span>Cover image</span></div>
      <p class="text-sm text-accent dark:text-accent-light font-medium mb-4 tracking-wide uppercase">Upstash</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-balance leading-tight">Distributed Lock SDK</h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal-muted dark:text-sand-muted">
        I built a distributed lock and debounce SDK on top of Upstash Redis for best-effort mutual exclusion in serverless applications.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="https://github.com/upstash/lock" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-ghost border border-cream-300 dark:border-ink-lighter">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@upstash/lock" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-ghost border border-cream-300 dark:border-ink-lighter">npm</a>
        <a href="https://upstash.com/blog/lock" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-ghost border border-cream-300 dark:border-ink-lighter">Launch post</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>Problem</h2>
      <p>
        Serverless and edge workloads often run the same expensive operation from multiple clients at once.
        Developers needed a small coordination primitive that could reduce duplicate work without managing
        a Redis deployment or long-lived infrastructure.
      </p>

      <h2>What I Built</h2>
      <p>
        I shipped <code>@upstash/lock</code>, a TypeScript package that provides distributed lock and debounce
        primitives using Upstash Redis. The package focused on efficiency use cases: avoiding duplicate
        expensive work, mostly-once execution, and simple coordination between stateless clients.
      </p>

      <h2>Tradeoffs</h2>
      <p>
        The package was explicit about its consistency model. Because Upstash Redis uses asynchronous
        replication, the SDK is intended for best-effort coordination rather than correctness-critical
        workflows like leader election or exactly-once execution.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .case-cover { display: grid; min-height: 18rem; place-items: center; border: 1px solid rgb(232 224 208); border-radius: 0.5rem; background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(47, 111, 159, 0.2) 25%, transparent 25%) 0 0 / 24px 24px, linear-gradient(135deg, transparent 75%, rgba(47, 111, 159, 0.16) 75%) 0 0 / 24px 24px, rgb(245 240 232); }
  :global(.dark) .case-cover { border-color: rgb(37 36 34); background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(59, 126, 161, 0.24) 25%, transparent 25%) 0 0 / 24px 24px, linear-gradient(135deg, transparent 75%, rgba(59, 126, 161, 0.18) 75%) 0 0 / 24px 24px, rgb(37 36 34); }
  .case-cover span { font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace; color: rgb(74 74 74); font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  :global(.dark) .case-cover span { color: rgb(184 180 172); }
</style>
